Currently, whenever a user searches something in JIRA (using JQL, for example), and then leaves the search navigation, the same JQL would still be stored for that user in such a way that the next time they perform a search, it would still use the same JQL as before.

However, this can cause some slowness when the user is using their JIRA, as their search is always stored in the memory. Although this slowness usually only occurs for the user, it sometimes can have a widespread effect on JIRA.

As such, it would be great if the search parameters would be removed or cleared when the user navigates away from the search.

